          "anchor": "Discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The argument you choose determines the rate at which the engine consumes user commands, performs internal updates, and executes callbacks.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When an app calls a PHASE function, the framework defers processing the call until the next update. An engine you configure with ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.phase/documentation/PHASE/PHASEEngine/UpdateMode/manual",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " controls when the framework processes those calls. For example, an app can ensure that two sound events begin simultaneously by following their creation with an ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.phase/documentation/PHASE/PHASEEngine/update()",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". Apps that donâ€™t require advanced call synchronization select ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.phase/documentation/PHASE/PHASEEngine/UpdateMode/automatic",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
